WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.970 --> 00:00:10.970
Should be far enough
from civilization out here.

2
00:00:11.050 --> 00:00:13.440
'cause who knows
what's about to go down.

3
00:00:14.690 --> 00:00:16.730
A job-change quest.

4
00:00:16.810 --> 00:00:20.210
I had to get to level 40
for this thing to even pop up.

5
00:00:21.270 --> 00:00:24.780
I don't need a key to access it like I
did with those other two dungeons.

6
00:00:24.860 --> 00:00:28.880
but it's also unlike the penalty
and emergency quests.

7
00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:32.140
since I wasn't forced into
carrying it out immediately.

8
00:00:33.410 --> 00:00:35.630
So it's optional.

9
00:00:35.710 --> 00:00:39.290
and I've been given plenty of time
to decide if I wanna do it or not.

10
00:00:39.370 --> 00:00:42.070
guess that means
it's gonna be more difficult.

11
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.240
But it's also safe to assume this will
let me earn skills best suited to my job.

12
00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:52.450
This quest will make me stronger.

13
00:00:55.230 --> 00:00:56.540
Yes.

14
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:04.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

15
00:01:08.320 --> 00:01:11.070
Uh. I forgot to do my daily quest.

16
00:01:11.150 --> 00:01:13.800
Eh. I can do it when I get back.

17
00:01:14.490 --> 00:01:16.250
All right. nice.

18
00:01:16.330 --> 00:01:20.210
It's almost like everything leading
up to this was prep for the real game.

19
00:01:20.290 --> 00:01:23.130
Wonder what sort of fun stuff
is waiting inside?

20
00:01:24.370 --> 00:01:26.280
Least it won't be boring.

21
00:03:18.450 --> 00:03:20.410
Sorry I'm late.

22
00:03:20.490 --> 00:03:23.020
Actually.
you're right on time. Jinsung.

23
00:03:23.830 --> 00:03:26.210
It's been quite a while. hasn't it?

24
00:03:26.290 --> 00:03:27.990
It has.

25
00:03:32.090 --> 00:03:34.110
Nothing out of the ordinary.

26
00:03:36.430 --> 00:03:37.810
What?

27
00:03:37.890 --> 00:03:41.270
I can't use potions or
full recovery in this place?

28
00:03:41.350 --> 00:03:43.970
I also can't leave
until I finish the quest.

29
00:03:44.050 --> 00:03:46.550
I'm gonna need to be extra careful.

30
00:03:57.820 --> 00:03:59.720
An armor-type beast.

31
00:04:07.170 --> 00:04:08.570
Hm.

32
00:04:17.470 --> 00:04:19.430
Not a scratch?

33
00:04:34.350 --> 00:04:36.110
You're durable.

34
00:04:38.660 --> 00:04:40.810
Tough to break that kind of armor.

35
00:04:43.750 --> 00:04:45.310
But...

36
00:04:47.170 --> 00:04:49.230
I've done it before!

37
00:04:58.380 --> 00:05:01.260
I wasted a Fatal Strike
on that beast.

38
00:05:01.340 --> 00:05:04.160
Can't recover my mana either
so that's great.

39
00:05:05.350 --> 00:05:06.860
But...

40
00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:09.980
It isn't like you tin cans care.

41
00:05:10.060 --> 00:05:11.460
Is it?

42
00:05:14.730 --> 00:05:16.570
What's wrong. Jinho?

43
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:18.780
You've barely touched
your food at all.

44
00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:20.470
N-nothing's wrong.

45
00:05:21.490 --> 00:05:25.420
Jinsung. how are things going
with establishing the guild?

46
00:05:25.500 --> 00:05:30.380
I heard the two S-Ranks you reached
out to have both declined your offer.

47
00:05:30.460 --> 00:05:32.250
Well. you heard correctly. then.

48
00:05:32.330 --> 00:05:35.050
Both Mister Min and
Miss Cha turned me down.

49
00:05:35.130 --> 00:05:36.890
But not to worry.

50
00:05:36.970 --> 00:05:41.120
I'm negotiating with hunters from
Europe and the Middle-east as we speak.

51
00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:45.650
They're likely to sign
if we agree to their terms.

52
00:05:45.730 --> 00:05:47.980
It will be similar to the case
of Dongsoo Hwang.

53
00:05:48.060 --> 00:05:49.520
Smart move.

54
00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:52.210
Yeah. very smart.

55
00:05:54.600 --> 00:05:56.470
-Jinho.
-Hm?

56
00:05:57.320 --> 00:06:00.820
I know that you've been working
on something of your own in secret.

57
00:06:00.900 --> 00:06:03.700
Going out of your way to buy
all these C-Rank gate rights.

58
00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:06.460
trying to establish
your hunting credentials.

59
00:06:06.540 --> 00:06:09.520
Which is fine.
for a personal project.

60
00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:12.850
if you stay in your lane.

61
00:06:16.920 --> 00:06:19.930
He thinks he knows.
but he has no idea.

62
00:06:20.010 --> 00:06:22.010
I have the boss on my side.

63
00:06:22.090 --> 00:06:24.570
And. with the power he has...

64
00:06:31.600 --> 00:06:34.900
Damn. even I'm tired
after fighting non-stop.

65
00:06:34.980 --> 00:06:37.050
I could use a break...

66
00:06:38.860 --> 00:06:40.820
Stealth?

67
00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:43.590
Now beasts are using that skill. too?

68
00:06:46.990 --> 00:06:51.000
And here comes a mage.
casting light magic. no less.

69
00:06:51.080 --> 00:06:52.870
What are the odds of that?

70
00:06:52.950 --> 00:06:54.790
Low. I'm sure.

71
00:06:54.870 --> 00:06:59.700
Add in the armor. and I'm
essentially reliving my past battles.

72
00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:04.780
I knew this quest
would be a tough one!

73
00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:10.520
Different kinds of beasts have
different kinds of weaknesses.

74
00:07:10.600 --> 00:07:16.280
You need strength for knights. perception
for assassins. and agility for archers.

75
00:07:16.360 --> 00:07:19.590
I wouldn't be able to damage
knights without enough strength.

76
00:07:23.070 --> 00:07:25.500
I wouldn't sense assassins
without enough perception.

77
00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:29.580
My weak spot. though. is mages.

78
00:07:29.660 --> 00:07:32.370
The Intellect stat's gotta
be the one that counters them.

79
00:07:32.450 --> 00:07:34.580
but it's also the one
I haven't invested in.

80
00:07:34.660 --> 00:07:38.740
Less intellect means less mana.
so I can't afford to waste skills.

81
00:07:42.590 --> 00:07:44.800
Then there's my fatigue.

82
00:07:44.880 --> 00:07:46.700
I need to end this!

83
00:07:59.150 --> 00:08:02.060
Excellent.
I do believe this is everyone.

84
00:08:04.150 --> 00:08:05.600
It's time.

85
00:08:14.950 --> 00:08:17.090
Beasts dropping canteens.

86
00:08:17.170 --> 00:08:19.630
Almost feel like
I should thank you guys.

87
00:08:20.510 --> 00:08:21.730
Huh?

88
00:08:22.670 --> 00:08:25.310
A High-Rank Knight's Chestplate?

89
00:08:25.390 --> 00:08:28.200
I haven't really experimented
with gear much.

90
00:08:33.800 --> 00:08:36.070
It's invisible. Nice.

91
00:08:36.150 --> 00:08:38.050
I'm glad I don't have to stand out.

92
00:08:40.190 --> 00:08:42.270
Doesn't restrict movement either.

93
00:08:42.350 --> 00:08:46.120
I'm not fully restored
yet so it's hard to tell.

94
00:08:46.200 --> 00:08:48.330
I leveled up. at least.

95
00:08:48.410 --> 00:08:50.490
Scored some gold and items. too.

96
00:08:50.570 --> 00:08:52.160
Fatigue's gone. so...

97
00:08:52.240 --> 00:08:53.830
Hm.

98
00:08:53.910 --> 00:08:56.730
I better go see what
the next stage has in store.

99
00:09:04.790 --> 00:09:08.220
Well. my next challenge
is waiting behind this door.

100
00:09:08.300 --> 00:09:11.200
Whatever it is. I have
a bad feeling about it.

101
00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:18.990
But if the only way out is through.
then. just have to press on.

102
00:09:26.240 --> 00:09:28.220
That's not a good sign.

103
00:09:46.630 --> 00:09:48.620
Some kind of throne room.

104
00:09:56.230 --> 00:09:58.480
It's different...

105
00:09:58.560 --> 00:10:02.440
but... also eerily similar.

106
00:10:02.520 --> 00:10:06.910
My body remembers this.
it's the same pressure I felt

107
00:10:06.990 --> 00:10:08.840
in the double dungeon.

108
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:16.190
All this intensity
is coming from him.

109
00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:20.870
Knight Commander Igris the Bloodred.

110
00:10:20.950 --> 00:10:22.900
Threat level's red. too.

111
00:10:23.700 --> 00:10:26.990
He's unlike anything
I've ever fought.

112
00:10:28.340 --> 00:10:31.360
A knight who defends an empty throne.

113
00:10:37.520 --> 00:10:39.040
Let's go!

114
00:10:47.610 --> 00:10:50.430
He cut that pillar like
it was a tree branch!

115
00:10:59.330 --> 00:11:01.390
This is beyond just strong!

116
00:11:12.460 --> 00:11:15.200
His heavy armor doesn't
slow him down at all.

117
00:11:28.980 --> 00:11:30.590
Still nothing!

118
00:11:43.910 --> 00:11:48.150
We're equals in terms of speed.
but he's way more powerful.

119
00:11:49.210 --> 00:11:51.530
And my dagger can't pierce his armor.

120
00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:55.030
Do I have any hope
of beating this guy?

121
00:11:56.800 --> 00:11:59.270
He's tougher than I first thought.

122
00:11:59.350 --> 00:12:01.350
Still...

123
00:12:01.430 --> 00:12:04.390
Different beasts
have different weaknesses.

124
00:12:04.470 --> 00:12:07.690
so if a weapon's not effective.
I'll just switch things up.

125
00:12:07.770 --> 00:12:09.460
Let's throw hands.

126
00:12:16.950 --> 00:12:19.220
Chivalry's not dead. I guess.

127
00:12:19.870 --> 00:12:21.890
Must think this'll be easy.

128
00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:27.980
Come in.

129
00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:31.340
I'm surprised you haven't gone
home for the evening. sir.

130
00:12:31.420 --> 00:12:33.880
I'm not quite ready to call it a day.

131
00:12:33.960 --> 00:12:36.760
Thought I'd tackle this stack
of work that's been piling up.

132
00:12:36.840 --> 00:12:38.600
Great minds think alike. then.

133
00:12:38.680 --> 00:12:41.910
I've been clearing some non-urgent
items off my plate. as well.

134
00:12:43.640 --> 00:12:45.010
It's really happening.

135
00:12:45.090 --> 00:12:46.460
Hm.

136
00:12:47.650 --> 00:12:49.860
Well. speak of the devil.

137
00:12:49.940 --> 00:12:52.520
Let me guess.
you're heading out soon.

138
00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:55.530
Yes. I can't express
how grateful I am

139
00:12:55.610 --> 00:12:58.450
you approved this operation.
but I'd still like to try.

140
00:12:58.530 --> 00:13:00.240
so thank you.

141
00:13:00.320 --> 00:13:02.160
No thanks needed.

142
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:05.540
You got the green light because
you kept Jeju's name afloat.

143
00:13:05.620 --> 00:13:09.250
All of those TV and print
interviews really paid off.

144
00:13:09.330 --> 00:13:11.960
Thanks to you. the island
has stayed relevant.

145
00:13:12.040 --> 00:13:15.000
and that helped sway public opinion.

146
00:13:15.080 --> 00:13:19.260
The only thing I'm responsible
for is tipping the scales a little.

147
00:13:19.340 --> 00:13:22.430
You don't expect criticism
for kicking a hornet's nest?

148
00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:24.640
I do. but I'll take the brunt of it.

149
00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:28.860
Just be careful out there.
Jeju Island is serious stuff.

150
00:13:28.940 --> 00:13:31.230
I'm fully aware. sir.

151
00:13:31.310 --> 00:13:33.770
Our main goal is
to assess threat levels.

152
00:13:33.850 --> 00:13:35.370
Well. for now. at least.

153
00:13:35.450 --> 00:13:38.240
We'll prod the enemy first
and gauge how they respond.

154
00:13:38.320 --> 00:13:41.280
As diligent as ever. I see.

155
00:13:41.360 --> 00:13:43.990
That third raid on Jeju...

156
00:13:44.070 --> 00:13:46.080
never really ended for me.

157
00:13:47.870 --> 00:13:50.270
It's like the battle
is still going on.

158
00:13:59.170 --> 00:14:00.870
So fast!

159
00:14:23.990 --> 00:14:25.580
I blocked him. but...

160
00:14:25.660 --> 00:14:28.620
I think I still lost 500 HP!

161
00:14:28.700 --> 00:14:31.060
Equipping armor was a good choice.

162
00:14:32.370 --> 00:14:35.270
Taking that attack full on
might've killed me.

163
00:14:36.130 --> 00:14:39.220
And that was without his damn sword!

164
00:14:39.300 --> 00:14:41.070
He's too strong!

165
00:14:43.710 --> 00:14:46.350
I can't compete
with his brute strength.

166
00:14:46.430 --> 00:14:48.290
but I have the speed!

167
00:15:04.980 --> 00:15:06.440
I can't...

168
00:15:13.200 --> 00:15:15.730
That passive skill raised my defense!

169
00:16:32.870 --> 00:16:34.350
That oughta do.

170
00:16:44.750 --> 00:16:46.160
Hm.

171
00:17:28.630 --> 00:17:30.370
No.

172
00:17:31.340 --> 00:17:32.720
I...

173
00:17:32.800 --> 00:17:36.660
haven't lost yet!

174
00:17:57.290 --> 00:17:59.630
That dagger can't change owners!

175
00:17:59.710 --> 00:18:02.900
It'll go to my inventory.
and then right back to me!

176
00:18:05.800 --> 00:18:08.700
Too shallow. stab deeper!

177
00:18:37.700 --> 00:18:40.520
I won. didn't I?

178
00:18:45.010 --> 00:18:47.670
Man. that was close.

179
00:18:50.300 --> 00:18:52.840
More of a fluke than a win.

180
00:18:52.920 --> 00:18:56.480
He had me beat in ability.
technique. experience.

181
00:18:56.560 --> 00:18:58.500
Surpassed me on every level.

182
00:18:59.470 --> 00:19:01.620
Death was one screw up away.

183
00:19:02.270 --> 00:19:05.190
Huh. I just got four rewards?

184
00:19:05.270 --> 00:19:08.490
A pouch with a
crap-ton of gold in it.

185
00:19:08.570 --> 00:19:11.780
And someone was kind enough
to leave me his helmet.

186
00:19:11.860 --> 00:19:13.450
Whoa. check the rank!

187
00:19:13.530 --> 00:19:16.460
Sure. the Demon's Castle key
was S-Rank. too.

188
00:19:16.540 --> 00:19:19.800
but this is the very first S-Rank
piece of gear I've earned.

189
00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:22.830
Huh. Reduces physical
damage by 15 percent.

190
00:19:22.910 --> 00:19:25.670
and gives a 20-point boost
to strength and vitality!

191
00:19:25.750 --> 00:19:27.550
Now we're talking.

192
00:19:27.630 --> 00:19:31.010
And uh. the Ruler's Hand stone.

193
00:19:31.090 --> 00:19:33.130
What skill is that?

194
00:19:33.210 --> 00:19:35.650
Guess I'll figure it out later.

195
00:19:36.760 --> 00:19:40.770
And lastly. a teleportation stone.

196
00:19:40.850 --> 00:19:43.520
It won't go in my inventory.

197
00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:46.340
Shouldn't this have dropped
before I beat the boss?

198
00:19:48.110 --> 00:19:52.090
Unless. no. don't tell me.

199
00:19:52.820 --> 00:19:54.630
This isn't over yet.

200
00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:04.080
So the quest begins now?

201
00:20:04.160 --> 00:20:06.820
What the hell?
What's this all about?

202
00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:10.590
Huh. Good luck. huh?

203
00:20:10.670 --> 00:20:12.110
Yeah. thanks.

204
00:20:12.960 --> 00:20:15.570
A timer? Is this infinite?

205
00:20:20.100 --> 00:20:25.140
If they were as strong as this one here.
I would be overwhelmed in seconds.

206
00:20:25.220 --> 00:20:28.650
But I can handle guys
like these easily enough.

207
00:20:28.730 --> 00:20:31.800
Though. there are quite a few.

208
00:20:47.580 --> 00:20:48.670
No good!

209
00:20:48.750 --> 00:20:53.030
I keep fighting. but the gates
keep puking up more and more!

210
00:20:54.500 --> 00:20:57.140
The whole point is to see
how long I last.

211
00:20:57.220 --> 00:20:58.990
So...

212
00:21:00.720 --> 00:21:07.070
Stealth costs 200 mana to activate.
then one mana every second it's in use.

213
00:21:07.150 --> 00:21:09.110
With 190 left.

214
00:21:09.190 --> 00:21:11.460
I can buy at least three minutes!

215
00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:17.890
They saw through Stealth?

216
00:21:19.410 --> 00:21:20.810
Damn!

217
00:21:27.120 --> 00:21:28.790
All right. then!

218
00:21:28.870 --> 00:21:31.150
No Stealth or Murderous Intent!

219
00:21:38.050 --> 00:21:40.010
How long's it been?

220
00:21:40.090 --> 00:21:41.930
Only five minutes?

221
00:21:42.010 --> 00:21:45.740
I can't keep going. I hate to.
but I've gotta use the stone.

222
00:21:46.305 --> 00:22:46.860
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
